text:
—I am just wondering why Senator Stott Despoja has just lifted the government's (ii) and put it as her (i). I think it is exactly the same, isn't it? It says:
because it would be unreasonable to expect the person to do so as there would be a serious risk to his or her physical or mental well-being due to violence, sexual abuse or other similar unreasonable circumstances;
That is there already. Those other ones taken together with what the committee has just done I see as dealing with the matter.
